RT by @satishacharya: Dear Mr. PM @narendramodi Ji, 
 
I have no affiliation to any political party. But as a common man and a tax paying citizen I have few questions for you, while I know they will not reach you but still the constitution of India gives me the right to ask тАШem:

1. Why is your party - party in power - The Government not letting the Parliament function. It costs 2.5 Lac per minute to every Tax payer of this Country.

2. How does criticizing you or your government become Anti - India. We are a nation of 140 Crore people. We have the right to criticize you or anyone in the Government on anything or wrong policies - That does not make anyone Anti-India. We donтАЩt choose our nation (mostly) but we do have the right to choose our government as per constitution every 5 years.

3. Despite being PM of India you campaign for your party on Public Exchequers money. You are PM of the Nation. Why do you campaign for your party on Tax Payers money, making several visits to poll bound states before elections, disguising under launching schemes. ItтАЩs our money which is getting swiped for your political gains.

4. You speak to your Australian counter part about attacks on Temples in his Country but turn a blind eye when a Masjid or a Church is vendalised in your own country under your own governance. 

The list is really long!!! I do not expect you to read or reply to this!!  While this is the harsh reality!!!

Being Prime Minister of this country, you donтАЩt act or behave, one!!! You are just a Prime Promoter of your Political Party!!!

Thanks!!! Jai Hind ЁЯЗоЁЯЗ│

#PMModi #Modi #QuestionstoPM #QuestioningGovernment #IndianPM
